text:
Eldert Street (left), south from Wyckoff Ave. to Long Island Railroad right of way, in a set of two views. No.1 shows the S.W. and No. 2 the S.E. corners. View No. 2 is in Brooklyn and View No. 2 shows the dividing line which is the center of the Street; and a line of garages on the Queens County side.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Eldert Street (left), south from Wyckoff Ave. to Long Island Railroad right of way, in a set of two views. No.1 shows the S.W. and No. 2 the S.E. corners. View No. 2 is in Brooklyn and View No. 2 shows the dividing line which is the center of the Street; and a line of garages on the Queens County side.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Eldert Street, north from the Manhattan Beach Railroad right of way to Wyckoff Ave.  The west side of Eldert Street is in Kings County.

October 1924.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Eldert Street, south from Wyckoff Ave. The center of this street is the dividing line between Kings and Queens Counties. The last named is on the east side of the Street.

October 1928.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
